WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.550 --> 00:00:13.220
(Gate rumbling. chains rattling)

2
00:00:42.420 --> 00:00:44.550
(Horse snorts)

3
00:00:57.430 --> 00:00:59.390
(Rumbling. chain rattling)

4
00:01:43.980 --> 00:01:45.650
(Wind whistling)

5
00:01:56.990 --> 00:01:59.250
- Easy. boy.

6
00:01:56.990 --> 00:01:59.250
- (Grunts)

7
00:03:00.770 --> 00:03:02.890
(Horse whinnies)

8
00:03:12.240 --> 00:03:14.280
(Man) What do you expect?

9
00:03:12.240 --> 00:03:14.280
They're savages.

10
00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:16.780
One lot steals a goat from another lot.

11
00:03:16.910 --> 00:03:19.240
before you know it

12
00:03:16.910 --> 00:03:19.240
they're ripping each other to pieces.

13
00:03:19.370 --> 00:03:21.830
I've never seen wildlings do a thing like this.

14
00:03:21.950 --> 00:03:24.120
I never seen a thing like this.

15
00:03:21.950 --> 00:03:24.120
not ever in my life.

16
00:03:24.250 --> 00:03:26.420
- (Horse snorts)

17
00:03:24.250 --> 00:03:26.420
- How close did you get?

18
00:03:26.540 --> 00:03:29.960
- Close as any man would.

19
00:03:26.540 --> 00:03:29.960
- We should head back to the Wall.

20
00:03:32.590 --> 00:03:34.050
Do the dead frighten you?

21
00:03:34.170 --> 00:03:36.300
Our orders were to track the wildlings.

22
00:03:36.430 --> 00:03:39.640
We tracked them.

23
00:03:36.430 --> 00:03:39.640
They won't trouble us no more.

24
00:03:39.760 --> 00:03:42.180
You don't think he'll ask us how they died?

25
00:03:44.430 --> 00:03:46.230
Get back on your horse.

26
00:03:47.810 --> 00:03:49.690
(Sighs. mutters)

27
00:03:50.940 --> 00:03:53.440
Whatever did it to them

28
00:03:50.940 --> 00:03:53.440
could do it to us.

29
00:03:53.570 --> 00:03:55.150
They even killed the children.

30
00:03:56.110 --> 00:03:58.110
It's a good thing we're not children.

31
00:03:59.490 --> 00:04:02.290
You want to run away south.

32
00:03:59.490 --> 00:04:02.290
run away.

33
00:04:02.410 --> 00:04:05.330
Of course.

34
00:04:02.410 --> 00:04:05.330
they will behead you as a deserter.

35
00:04:05.460 --> 00:04:07.580
If I don't catch you first.

36
00:04:09.960 --> 00:04:12.250
Get back on your horse.

37
00:04:12.380 --> 00:04:14.710
I won't say it again.

38
00:04:32.360 --> 00:04:34.530
(Shrill animal call)

39
00:04:45.830 --> 00:04:48.330
Your dead men seem

40
00:04:45.830 --> 00:04:48.330
to have moved camp.

41
00:04:49.040 --> 00:04:50.710
They were here.

42
00:04:54.090 --> 00:04:55.760
See where they went.

43
00:05:11.190 --> 00:05:13.860
(Echoing creature cries)

44
00:05:42.260 --> 00:05:44.140
What is it?

45
00:05:45.430 --> 00:05:46.560
It's...

46
00:05:47.640 --> 00:05:49.520
(Cracking. creaking)

47
00:05:51.850 --> 00:05:53.940
(Distant scream)

48
00:05:54.060 --> 00:05:56.230
(Horses neighing)

49
00:05:56.360 --> 00:05:58.070
(Galloping hooves)

50
00:06:26.760 --> 00:06:27.850
(Snarling)

51
00:06:29.720 --> 00:06:31.100
(Chittering)

52
00:06:40.280 --> 00:06:42.240
(Coughing)

53
00:06:44.110 --> 00:06:45.910
(Coughing)

54
00:06:46.030 --> 00:06:48.030
(Panting)

55
00:06:48.160 --> 00:06:49.910
(Labored breathing)

56
00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:52.830
(Snarling)

57
00:06:55.290 --> 00:06:56.960
(Gasps)

58
00:07:01.840 --> 00:07:03.470
(Crackling)

59
00:07:11.890 --> 00:07:13.560
(Chittering)

60
00:09:01.080 --> 00:09:03.090
(Galloping hooves)

61
00:09:43.540 --> 00:09:44.960
(Stamps)

62
00:09:49.630 --> 00:09:52.090
Go on. Father's watching.

63
00:09:54.300 --> 00:09:56.010
And your mother.

64
00:10:02.190 --> 00:10:05.520
Fine work. as always.

65
00:10:02.190 --> 00:10:05.520
Well done.

66
00:10:05.650 --> 00:10:07.320
Thank you.

67
00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:11.280
I love the detail that you've managed

68
00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:11.280
to get in these corners.

69
00:10:11.400 --> 00:10:13.200
Quite beautiful.

70
00:10:13.320 --> 00:10:15.200
The stitching...

71
00:10:15.320 --> 00:10:17.540
Oh. no. no. no. This stitch is very...

72
00:10:17.660 --> 00:10:19.120
(Arrows impacting. men laughing)

73
00:10:19.250 --> 00:10:21.210
- It's beautiful.

74
00:10:19.250 --> 00:10:21.210
- Thank you.

75
00:10:28.380 --> 00:10:30.460
(Arrow impacting)

76
00:10:34.220 --> 00:10:36.260
- (Sighs)

77
00:10:34.220 --> 00:10:36.260
- (Laughing)

78
00:10:36.390 --> 00:10:39.140
And which one of you

79
00:10:36.390 --> 00:10:39.140
was a marksman at ten?

80
00:10:40.180 --> 00:10:41.680
Keep practicing. Bran.

81
00:10:43.850 --> 00:10:45.810
Go on.

82
00:10:45.940 --> 00:10:48.610
Don't think too much. Bran.

83
00:10:51.030 --> 00:10:52.190
Relax your bow arm.

84
00:11:02.290 --> 00:11:04.170
(Men laughing)

85
00:11:05.330 --> 00:11:06.830
- Quick. Bran!

86
00:11:05.330 --> 00:11:06.830
- Faster.

87
00:11:08.420 --> 00:11:10.420
Lord Stark!

88
00:11:12.460 --> 00:11:13.510
My lady.

89
00:11:14.550 --> 00:11:16.760
A guardsman just rode in from the hills.

90
00:11:16.890 --> 00:11:19.890
They've captured a deserter

91
00:11:16.890 --> 00:11:19.890
from the Night's Watch.

92
00:11:23.180 --> 00:11:25.310
Get the lads to saddle their horses.

93
00:11:25.440 --> 00:11:27.400
Do you have to?

94
00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:29.610
He swore an oath. Cat.

95
00:11:29.730 --> 00:11:31.730
Law is law. my lady.

96
00:11:32.740 --> 00:11:34.820
Tell Bran he's coming too.

97
00:11:36.740 --> 00:11:38.320
Ned.

98
00:11:38.450 --> 00:11:40.740
Ten is too young

99
00:11:38.450 --> 00:11:40.740
to see such things.

100
00:11:40.870 --> 00:11:42.410
He won't be a boy forever.

101
00:11:44.410 --> 00:11:46.080
And winter is coming.

102
00:12:05.230 --> 00:12:07.440
Good lad. go run back and get the rest.

103
00:12:13.570 --> 00:12:15.150
White walkers.

104
00:12:15.280 --> 00:12:17.990
I saw the white walkers.

105
00:12:18.110 --> 00:12:19.990
White walkers.

106
00:12:20.120 --> 00:12:23.160
The white walkers. I saw them.

107
00:12:23.290 --> 00:12:24.910
(Exhales)

108
00:12:31.960 --> 00:12:33.590
I know I broke my oath.

109
00:12:34.800 --> 00:12:36.300
And I know I'm a deserter.

110
00:12:37.170 --> 00:12:39.840
I should have gone back to the Wall

111
00:12:37.170 --> 00:12:39.840
and warned them. but...

112
00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:43.010
I saw what I saw.

113
00:12:43.140 --> 00:12:44.680
I saw the white walkers.

114
00:12:46.640 --> 00:12:48.480
People need to know.

115
00:12:50.650 --> 00:12:52.480
If you can get word to my family...

116
00:12:52.610 --> 00:12:54.900
tell them I'm no coward.

117
00:12:55.030 --> 00:12:56.990
Tell them I'm sorry.

118
00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:15.670
(Whispers) Forgive me. Lord.

119
00:13:20.050 --> 00:13:22.220
In the name of Robert

120
00:13:20.050 --> 00:13:22.220
of the House Baratheon.

121
00:13:22.340 --> 00:13:24.310
- the first of his name...

122
00:13:22.340 --> 00:13:24.310
- Don't look away.

123
00:13:24.430 --> 00:13:27.270
- ..King of the Andals and the First Men...

124
00:13:24.430 --> 00:13:27.270
- Father will know if you do.

125
00:13:27.390 --> 00:13:30.730
..Lord of the Seven Kingdoms

126
00:13:27.390 --> 00:13:30.730
and protector of the realm.

127
00:13:30.850 --> 00:13:33.730
I. Eddard of the House Stark.

128
00:13:33.860 --> 00:13:36.400
Lord of Winterfell

129
00:13:33.860 --> 00:13:36.400
and Warden of the North.

130
00:13:36.530 --> 00:13:38.990
sentence you to die.

131
00:13:53.790 --> 00:13:55.460
You did well.

132
00:14:23.660 --> 00:14:25.120
You understand why I did it?

133
00:14:25.240 --> 00:14:27.120
Jon said he was a deserter.

134
00:14:27.240 --> 00:14:29.790
But do you understand

135
00:14:27.240 --> 00:14:29.790
why I had to kill him?

136
00:14:29.910 --> 00:14:31.540
"Our way is the old way"?

137
00:14:33.170 --> 00:14:36.840
The man who passes the sentence

138
00:14:33.170 --> 00:14:36.840
should swing the sword.

139
00:14:37.880 --> 00:14:40.260
Is it true he saw the white walkers?

140
00:14:42.300 --> 00:14:45.260
The white walkers have been gone

141
00:14:42.300 --> 00:14:45.260
for thousands of years.

142
00:14:46.430 --> 00:14:47.930
So he was lying?

143
00:14:52.430 --> 00:14:54.770
A madman sees what he sees.

144
00:15:20.710 --> 00:15:22.630
What is it?

145
00:15:25.010 --> 00:15:26.680
Mountain lion?

146
00:15:28.050 --> 00:15:30.390
There are no mountain lions

147
00:15:28.050 --> 00:15:30.390
in these woods.

148
00:15:57.670 --> 00:15:59.330
(Pup whines)

149
00:16:16.560 --> 00:16:18.350
It's a freak.

150
00:16:19.730 --> 00:16:21.020
It's a direwolf.

151
00:16:30.280 --> 00:16:32.530
Tough old beast.

152
00:16:34.830 --> 00:16:36.910
There are no direwolves

153
00:16:34.830 --> 00:16:36.910
south of the Wall.

154
00:16:37.790 --> 00:16:39.080
Now there are five.

155
00:16:40.710 --> 00:16:42.380
You want to hold it?

156
00:16:43.880 --> 00:16:46.010
(Pup whimpers)

157
00:16:46.920 --> 00:16:48.430
(Bran) Where will they go?

158
00:16:48.550 --> 00:16:50.260
Their mother's dead.

159
00:16:50.390 --> 00:16:51.930
They don't belong down here.

160
00:16:52.050 --> 00:16:55.850
Better a quick death.

161
00:16:52.050 --> 00:16:55.850
They won't last without their mother.

162
00:16:55.970 --> 00:16:57.980
- Right. Give it here.

163
00:16:55.970 --> 00:16:57.980
- No!

164
00:16:58.100 --> 00:16:59.770
- (Whimpers)

165
00:16:58.100 --> 00:16:59.770
- Put away your blade.

166
00:16:59.900 --> 00:17:02.810
- I take orders from your father. not you.

167
00:16:59.900 --> 00:17:02.810
- Please. Father!

168
00:17:02.940 --> 00:17:04.730
I'm sorry. Bran.

169
00:17:04.860 --> 00:17:05.900
Lord Stark?

170
00:17:07.690 --> 00:17:09.200
There are five pups.

171
00:17:10.570 --> 00:17:12.660
One for each of the Stark children.

172
00:17:12.780 --> 00:17:15.290
- (Pup cries)

173
00:17:12.780 --> 00:17:15.290
- The direwolf is the sigil of your house.

174
00:17:16.660 --> 00:17:18.870
They were meant to have them.

175
00:17:24.130 --> 00:17:26.300
You will train them yourselves.

176
00:17:26.420 --> 00:17:28.300
You will feed them yourselves.

177
00:17:28.420 --> 00:17:31.300
And if they die. you will bury them yourselves.

178
00:17:39.940 --> 00:17:41.650
What about you?

179
00:17:42.520 --> 00:17:44.190
I'm not a Stark.

180
00:17:44.310 --> 00:17:46.400
Get on.

181
00:17:53.410 --> 00:17:55.490
(Whimpering)

182
00:17:56.450 --> 00:17:57.910
What is it?

183
00:18:02.120 --> 00:18:05.630
The runt of the litter.

184
00:18:02.120 --> 00:18:05.630
That one's yours. Snow.

185
00:18:14.760 --> 00:18:16.310
(Bells tolling)

186
00:19:05.810 --> 00:19:08.980
As your brother.

187
00:19:05.810 --> 00:19:08.980
I feel it's my duty to warn you...

188
00:19:10.230 --> 00:19:12.240
you worry too much.

189
00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:15.700
- It's starting to show.

190
00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:15.700
- And you never worry about anything.

191
00:19:16.990 --> 00:19:20.910
When we were seven and you jumped off

192
00:19:16.990 --> 00:19:20.910
the cliffs at Casterly Rock.

193
00:19:21.040 --> 00:19:25.420
100-foot drop into the water...

194
00:19:21.040 --> 00:19:25.420
you were never afraid.

195
00:19:25.540 --> 00:19:28.170
There was nothing to be afraid of

196
00:19:25.540 --> 00:19:28.170
until you told Father.

197
00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:31.880
(Mimics) "We're Lannisters.

198
00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:31.880
Lannisters don't act like fools."

199
00:19:34.300 --> 00:19:37.840
- What if Jon Arryn told someone?

200
00:19:34.300 --> 00:19:37.840
- But who would he tell?

201
00:19:39.220 --> 00:19:40.350
My husband.

202
00:19:40.470 --> 00:19:44.230
If he told the king. both our heads would be

203
00:19:40.470 --> 00:19:44.230
skewered on the city gates by now.

204
00:19:45.770 --> 00:19:48.900
Whatever Jon Arryn knew or didn't know.

205
00:19:45.770 --> 00:19:48.900
it died with him.

206
00:19:49.770 --> 00:19:51.610
And Robert will choose

207
00:19:49.770 --> 00:19:51.610
a new Hand of the King.

208
00:19:51.730 --> 00:19:55.320
someone to do his job while he's off

209
00:19:51.730 --> 00:19:55.320
fucking boars and hunting whores.

210
00:19:55.450 --> 00:19:57.110
Or is it the other way around?

211
00:19:58.660 --> 00:20:00.990
And life will go on.

212
00:20:01.120 --> 00:20:03.700
You should be the Hand of the King.

213
00:20:04.580 --> 00:20:06.420
That's an honor I can do without.

214
00:20:06.540 --> 00:20:08.170
Their days are too long.

215
00:20:08.290 --> 00:20:09.960
their lives are too short.

216
00:20:15.510 --> 00:20:17.220
(Thunder rumbles)

217
00:20:22.760 --> 00:20:23.770
(Caws)

218
00:20:38.160 --> 00:20:39.820
(Birds chirping)

219
00:20:49.500 --> 00:20:50.710
All these years.

220
00:20:50.830 --> 00:20:53.960
and I still feel like an outsider

221
00:20:50.830 --> 00:20:53.960
when I come here.

222
00:20:55.800 --> 00:20:57.470
You have five northern children.

223
00:20:58.720 --> 00:21:01.010
You're not an outsider.

224
00:21:01.140 --> 00:21:03.640
I wonder if the old gods agree.

225
00:21:04.890 --> 00:21:06.770
It's your gods with all the rules.

226
00:21:13.520 --> 00:21:15.860
I am so sorry. my love.

227
00:21:16.990 --> 00:21:20.610
- Tell me.

228
00:21:16.990 --> 00:21:20.610
- There was a raven from King's Landing.

229
00:21:22.740 --> 00:21:24.280
Jon Arryn is dead.

230
00:21:24.410 --> 00:21:26.910
A fever took him.

231
00:21:29.830 --> 00:21:31.960
I know he was like a father to you.

232
00:21:35.090 --> 00:21:38.130
- Your sister. the boy?

233
00:21:35.090 --> 00:21:38.130
- They both have their health.

234
00:21:38.260 --> 00:21:40.260
gods be good.

235
00:21:50.520 --> 00:21:51.850
The raven brought more news.

236
00:21:53.980 --> 00:21:56.360
The king rides for Winterfell...

237
00:21:57.400 --> 00:22:00.200
with the queen and all the rest of them.

238
00:22:01.110 --> 00:22:03.450
If he's coming this far north...

239
00:22:05.120 --> 00:22:07.040
there's only one thing he's after.

240
00:22:07.160 --> 00:22:10.540
You can always say no. Ned.

241
00:22:18.880 --> 00:22:22.590
(Catelyn) We'll need plenty of candles

242
00:22:18.880 --> 00:22:22.590
for Lord Tyrion's chamber.

243
00:22:22.720 --> 00:22:26.470
- I'm told he reads all night.

244
00:22:22.720 --> 00:22:26.470
- I'm told he drinks all night.

245
00:22:26.600 --> 00:22:29.770
How much could he possibly drink?

246
00:22:26.600 --> 00:22:29.770
A man of his...

247
00:22:29.890 --> 00:22:31.430
stature?

248
00:22:31.560 --> 00:22:34.440
We've brought up eight barrels of ale

249
00:22:31.560 --> 00:22:34.440
from the cellar.

250
00:22:34.560 --> 00:22:35.770
Perhaps we'll find out.

251
00:22:35.900 --> 00:22:37.730
In any case. candles.

252
00:22:43.860 --> 00:22:46.780
Why is your mother so dead set on us

253
00:22:43.860 --> 00:22:46.780
getting pretty for the king?

254
00:22:46.910 --> 00:22:49.660
It's for the queen. I bet.

255
00:22:46.910 --> 00:22:49.660
I hear she's a sleek bit of mink.

256
00:22:49.790 --> 00:22:51.830
I hear the prince is a right royal prick.

257
00:22:51.960 --> 00:22:55.420
Think of all those southern girls he gets to stab

258
00:22:51.960 --> 00:22:55.420
with his right royal prick.

259
00:22:57.340 --> 00:22:59.460
Go on. Tommy. shear him good.

260
00:22:59.590 --> 00:23:01.880
He's never met a girl he likes better

261
00:22:59.590 --> 00:23:01.880
than his own hair.

262
00:23:02.010 --> 00:23:03.720
(Laughter)

263
00:23:38.880 --> 00:23:41.550
- (Pup yaps)

264
00:23:38.880 --> 00:23:41.550
- Gods. but they grow fast.

265
00:23:44.010 --> 00:23:45.510
Brandon!

266
00:23:45.630 --> 00:23:48.640
I saw the king.

267
00:23:45.630 --> 00:23:48.640
He's got hundreds of people.

268
00:23:48.760 --> 00:23:51.850
How many times have I told you?

269
00:23:48.760 --> 00:23:51.850
No climbing.

270
00:23:51.970 --> 00:23:54.940
But he's coming right now. down our road.

271
00:24:01.940 --> 00:24:04.360
I want you to promise me.

272
00:24:04.490 --> 00:24:06.150
no more climbing.

273
00:24:10.990 --> 00:24:12.160
I promise.

274
00:24:14.330 --> 00:24:17.370
- Do you know what?

275
00:24:14.330 --> 00:24:17.370
- What?

276
00:24:17.500 --> 00:24:19.710
You always look at your feet

277
00:24:17.500 --> 00:24:19.710
before you lie.

278
00:24:19.830 --> 00:24:21.750
(Chuckles)

279
00:24:21.880 --> 00:24:23.630
Run and find your father.

280
00:24:23.760 --> 00:24:25.800
Tell him the king is close.

281
00:25:10.220 --> 00:25:13.600
Where's Arya?

282
00:25:10.220 --> 00:25:13.600
Sansa. where's your sister?

283
00:25:23.900 --> 00:25:26.070
- Hey. hey. hey. hey.

284
00:25:23.900 --> 00:25:26.070
- Oh.

285
00:25:26.190 --> 00:25:28.110
What are you doing with that on?

286
00:25:30.530 --> 00:25:32.620
- Go on.

287
00:25:30.530 --> 00:25:32.620
- (Groans)

288
00:25:33.990 --> 00:25:35.660
(Arya) Move!

289
00:25:53.300 --> 00:25:55.390
(Neighs)

290
00:26:57.830 --> 00:26:59.660
Your Grace.

291
00:27:04.170 --> 00:27:05.830
You've got fat.

292
00:27:12.510 --> 00:27:14.180
(Laughter)

293
00:27:17.930 --> 00:27:19.470
- Cat!

294
00:27:17.930 --> 00:27:19.470
- Your Grace.

295
00:27:23.600 --> 00:27:27.060
Nine years... Why haven't I seen you?

296
00:27:23.600 --> 00:27:27.060
Where the hell have you been?

297
00:27:27.190 --> 00:27:30.730
Guarding the North for you. Your Grace.

298
00:27:27.190 --> 00:27:30.730
Winterfell is yours.

299
00:27:34.650 --> 00:27:37.200
- Where's the Imp?

300
00:27:34.650 --> 00:27:37.200
- Will you shut up?

301
00:27:37.320 --> 00:27:38.830
(Robert) Who have we here?

302
00:27:40.200 --> 00:27:41.540
You must be Robb.

303
00:27:44.500 --> 00:27:46.620
My. you're a pretty one.

304
00:27:48.040 --> 00:27:49.920
Your name is?

305
00:27:50.040 --> 00:27:51.420
Arya.

306
00:27:52.630 --> 00:27:55.220
Oh. show us your muscles.

307
00:27:56.550 --> 00:27:58.850
(Chuckles) You'll be a soldier.

308
00:28:01.720 --> 00:28:04.140
(Arya) That's Jaime Lannister.

309
00:28:01.720 --> 00:28:04.140
the queen's twin brother.

310
00:28:04.270 --> 00:28:06.390
(Sansa) Would you please shut up?

311
00:28:15.950 --> 00:28:16.950
My queen.

312
00:28:18.240 --> 00:28:19.820
My queen.

313
00:28:19.950 --> 00:28:21.950
Take me to your crypt.

314
00:28:19.950 --> 00:28:21.950
I want to pay my respects.

315
00:28:22.080 --> 00:28:23.910
We've been riding for a month. my love.

316
00:28:24.410 --> 00:28:26.040
Surely the dead can wait.

317
00:28:26.160 --> 00:28:28.040
Ned.

318
00:28:37.720 --> 00:28:38.930
Where's the Imp?

319
00:28:42.430 --> 00:28:44.430
(Queen) Where is our brother?

320
00:28:44.560 --> 00:28:46.310
Go and find the little beast.

321
00:28:48.690 --> 00:28:50.360
Tell me about Jon Arryn.

322
00:28:51.610 --> 00:28:53.820
One minute he was fine and then...

323
00:28:55.030 --> 00:28:57.780
burned right through him.

324
00:28:55.030 --> 00:28:57.780
whatever it was.

325
00:28:58.950 --> 00:29:00.950
I loved that man.

326
00:29:01.070 --> 00:29:02.410
We both did.

327
00:29:02.530 --> 00:29:06.870
(Robert) He never had to teach you much.

328
00:29:02.530 --> 00:29:06.870
but me? You remember me at 16?

329
00:29:07.000 --> 00:29:08.830
- (Chuckles)

330
00:29:07.000 --> 00:29:08.830
- All I wanted to do

331
00:29:08.960 --> 00:29:11.580
was crack skulls and fuck girls.

332
00:29:11.710 --> 00:29:14.840
- He showed me what was what.

333
00:29:11.710 --> 00:29:14.840
- Aye.

334
00:29:14.960 --> 00:29:17.590
Don't look at me like that.

335
00:29:14.960 --> 00:29:17.590
It's not his fault I didn't listen.

336
00:29:17.720 --> 00:29:19.550
(Both laugh)

337
00:29:20.300 --> 00:29:22.010
(Sighs)

338
00:29:22.140 --> 00:29:24.180
I need you. Ned.

339
00:29:24.310 --> 00:29:27.980
down at King's Landing. not up here

340
00:29:24.310 --> 00:29:27.980
where you're no damn use to anybody.

341
00:29:29.850 --> 00:29:31.650
Lord Eddard Stark...

342
00:29:32.610 --> 00:29:35.070
I would name you the Hand of the King.

343
00:29:39.530 --> 00:29:41.660
I'm not worthy of the honor.

344
00:29:41.780 --> 00:29:43.200
I'm not trying to honor you.

345
00:29:43.320 --> 00:29:45.030
I'm trying to get you to run my kingdom

346
00:29:45.160 --> 00:29:48.870
while I eat. drink and whore my way

347
00:29:45.160 --> 00:29:48.870
to an early grave.

348
00:29:49.000 --> 00:29:50.830
Damn it. Ned. stand up.

349
00:29:52.380 --> 00:29:54.340
You helped me win the Iron Throne.

350
00:29:54.460 --> 00:29:57.170
now help me keep the damn thing.

351
00:29:57.300 --> 00:29:59.670
We were meant to rule together.

352
00:29:59.800 --> 00:30:03.640
If your sister had lived.

353
00:29:59.800 --> 00:30:03.640
we'd have been bound by blood.

354
00:30:04.600 --> 00:30:06.180
Well. it's not too late.

355
00:30:07.850 --> 00:30:09.520
I have a son.

356
00:30:07.850 --> 00:30:09.520
you have a daughter.

357
00:30:11.350 --> 00:30:13.020
We'll join our houses.

358
00:30:17.360 --> 00:30:19.030
(Woman moaning)

359
00:30:30.870 --> 00:30:32.040
(Sighs)

360
00:30:37.170 --> 00:30:38.090
(Cup falls)

361
00:30:38.210 --> 00:30:41.170
It is true what they say

362
00:30:38.210 --> 00:30:41.170
about the northern girls.

363
00:30:41.300 --> 00:30:42.380
(Giggles)

364
00:30:49.390 --> 00:30:51.730
Did you hear the king's in Winterfell?

365
00:30:51.850 --> 00:30:53.480
I did hear something about that.

366
00:30:53.600 --> 00:30:55.770
And the queen and her twin brother.

367
00:30:55.900 --> 00:30:58.940
They say that he is the most handsome man

368
00:30:55.900 --> 00:30:58.940
in the Seven Kingdoms.

369
00:30:59.070 --> 00:31:00.940
And the other brother?

370
00:31:01.070 --> 00:31:04.280
- The queen has two brothers?

371
00:31:01.070 --> 00:31:04.280
- There's the pretty one...

372
00:31:05.490 --> 00:31:07.200
and there's the clever one.

373
00:31:08.490 --> 00:31:09.990
Mmm...

374
00:31:10.120 --> 00:31:12.370
I hear they call him the Imp.

375
00:31:12.500 --> 00:31:14.290
I hear he hates that nickname.

376
00:31:14.420 --> 00:31:17.790
Oh? I hear he's more than earned it.

377
00:31:17.920 --> 00:31:20.170
I hear he's a drunken little lecher.

378
00:31:20.300 --> 00:31:22.760
prone to all manner of perversions.

379
00:31:22.880 --> 00:31:24.680
Clever girl.

380
00:31:26.430 --> 00:31:28.260
We've been expecting you. Lord Tyrion.

381
00:31:29.600 --> 00:31:31.180
Have you?

382
00:31:31.310 --> 00:31:32.680
- Already?

383
00:31:31.310 --> 00:31:32.680
- Oh!

384
00:31:35.600 --> 00:31:38.310
- The gods gave me one blessing.

385
00:31:35.600 --> 00:31:38.310
- (Laughs)

386
00:31:38.440 --> 00:31:39.480
(Door opens)

387
00:31:43.190 --> 00:31:45.700
- Don't get up.

388
00:31:43.190 --> 00:31:45.700
- My lord.

389
00:31:45.820 --> 00:31:49.490
Should I explain to you the meaning of

390
00:31:45.820 --> 00:31:49.490
a closed door in a whorehouse. brother?

391
00:31:49.620 --> 00:31:51.660
You have much to teach me. no doubt.

392
00:31:51.790 --> 00:31:54.960
but our sister craves your attention.

393
00:31:55.670 --> 00:31:57.670
She has odd cravings. our sister.

394
00:31:57.790 --> 00:31:59.840
A family trait.

395
00:31:59.960 --> 00:32:02.420
Now. the Starks are feasting us at sundown.

396
00:32:03.420 --> 00:32:07.390
- Don't leave me alone with these people.

397
00:32:03.420 --> 00:32:07.390
- I'm sorry. I've begun the feast a bit early.

398
00:32:07.510 --> 00:32:10.850
And this is the first of many courses.

399
00:32:10.970 --> 00:32:13.180
I thought you might say that.

400
00:32:13.310 --> 00:32:15.940
But since we're short on time...

401
00:32:16.060 --> 00:32:17.350
Come on. girls.

402
00:32:17.480 --> 00:32:20.110
(Giggling)

403
00:32:23.320 --> 00:32:25.110
See you at sundown.

404
00:32:25.240 --> 00:32:27.320
(Tyrion) Close the door!

405
00:32:39.750 --> 00:32:42.500
Did you have to bury her

406
00:32:39.750 --> 00:32:42.500
in a place like this?

407
00:32:44.380 --> 00:32:46.590
She should be on a hill somewhere

408
00:32:46.720 --> 00:32:49.050
with the sun and the clouds above her.

409
00:32:49.180 --> 00:32:51.220
She was my sister.

410
00:32:51.350 --> 00:32:53.010
This is where she belongs.

411
00:32:54.180 --> 00:32:56.520
She belonged with me.

412
00:33:01.980 --> 00:33:05.190
In my dreams.

413
00:33:01.980 --> 00:33:05.190
I kill him every night.

414
00:33:06.740 --> 00:33:11.030
It's done. Your Grace.

415
00:33:06.740 --> 00:33:11.030
The Targaryens are gone.

416
00:33:14.240 --> 00:33:16.160
Not all of them.

417
00:33:17.790 --> 00:33:19.580
(Gull crying)

418
00:33:27.090 --> 00:33:29.050
(Man) Daenerys!

419
00:33:32.220 --> 00:33:33.930
Daenerys.

420
00:33:34.060 --> 00:33:36.060
There's our bride-to-be.

421
00:33:37.060 --> 00:33:39.640
Look. a gift from Illyrio.

422
00:33:41.230 --> 00:33:42.810
Touch it.

423
00:33:42.940 --> 00:33:45.150
Go on. feel the fabric.

424
00:33:50.070 --> 00:33:51.070
Mmm.

425
00:33:53.240 --> 00:33:55.080
Isn't he a gracious host?

426
00:33:58.450 --> 00:34:02.120
We've been his guests for over a year

427
00:33:58.450 --> 00:34:02.120
and he's never asked us for anything.

428
00:34:02.250 --> 00:34:04.130
Illyrio's no fool.

429
00:34:04.250 --> 00:34:06.050
He knows I won't forget my friends

430
00:34:06.170 --> 00:34:08.420
when I come into my throne.

431
00:34:12.760 --> 00:34:14.510
You still slouch.

432
00:34:18.890 --> 00:34:21.190
Let them see.

433
00:34:23.980 --> 00:34:26.730
You have a woman's body now.

434
00:34:29.690 --> 00:34:31.400
(Sighs)

435
00:34:44.630 --> 00:34:46.630
I need you to be perfect today.

436
00:34:49.170 --> 00:34:50.550
Can you do that for me?

437
00:34:54.090 --> 00:34:56.680
You don't want to wake the dragon. do you?

438
00:34:58.640 --> 00:34:59.680
No.

439
00:35:06.810 --> 00:35:09.400
When they write the history

440
00:35:06.810 --> 00:35:09.400
of my reign. sweet sister.

441
00:35:09.530 --> 00:35:11.490
they will say it began today.

442
00:35:35.220 --> 00:35:36.890
It's too hot. my lady.

443
00:35:47.980 --> 00:35:49.650
(Gulls crying)

444
00:35:58.160 --> 00:36:00.080
Where is he?

445
00:36:00.200 --> 00:36:03.080
The Dothraki are not known

446
00:36:00.200 --> 00:36:03.080
for their punctuality.

447
00:36:16.380 --> 00:36:20.430
(Illyrio speaks Dothraki)

448
00:36:20.550 --> 00:36:22.470
May I present my honored guests?

449
00:36:22.600 --> 00:36:26.140
Viserys of House Targaryen.

450
00:36:26.270 --> 00:36:27.770
the third of his name.

451
00:36:27.900 --> 00:36:31.270
the rightful King of the Andals

452
00:36:27.900 --> 00:36:31.270
and the First Men.

453
00:36:31.400 --> 00:36:32.690
and his sister.

454
00:36:32.820 --> 00:36:35.700
Daenerys of House Targaryen.

455
00:36:36.780 --> 00:36:38.610
(Speaks Dothraki)

456
00:36:38.740 --> 00:36:41.160
Do you see how long his hair is?

457
00:36:41.280 --> 00:36:44.080
When Dothraki are defeated in combat

458
00:36:44.200 --> 00:36:47.790
they cut off their braid

459
00:36:44.200 --> 00:36:47.790
so the whole world can see their shame.

460
00:36:47.920 --> 00:36:51.750
Khal Drogo has never been defeated.

461
00:36:53.210 --> 00:36:57.090
He's a savage. of course.

462
00:36:53.210 --> 00:36:57.090
but he's one of the finest killers alive.

463
00:36:58.470 --> 00:37:00.590
And you will be his queen.

464
00:37:01.390 --> 00:37:03.260
Come forward. my dear.

465
00:37:43.390 --> 00:37:44.510
Where is he going?

466
00:37:44.640 --> 00:37:47.350
- The ceremony is over.

467
00:37:44.640 --> 00:37:47.350
- But he... But he didn't say anything.

468
00:37:47.480 --> 00:37:48.600
Did he like her?

469
00:37:48.730 --> 00:37:52.480
Trust me. Your Grace.

470
00:37:48.730 --> 00:37:52.480
if he didn't like her. we'd know.

471
00:37:55.610 --> 00:37:57.860
(Illyrio) It won't be long now.

472
00:37:57.990 --> 00:38:01.610
Soon you will cross the narrow sea

473
00:37:57.990 --> 00:38:01.610
and take back your father's throne.

474
00:38:02.870 --> 00:38:06.700
The people drink secret toasts

475
00:38:02.870 --> 00:38:06.700
to your health.

476
00:38:06.830 --> 00:38:09.290
They cry out for their true king.

477
00:38:12.830 --> 00:38:14.710
When will they be married?

478
00:38:14.840 --> 00:38:18.380
Soon.

479
00:38:14.840 --> 00:38:18.380
The Dothraki never stay still for long.

480
00:38:18.510 --> 00:38:20.760
Is it true they lie with their horses?

481
00:38:21.510 --> 00:38:23.800
I wouldn't ask Khal Drogo.

482
00:38:23.930 --> 00:38:26.060
Do you take me for a fool?

483
00:38:26.180 --> 00:38:27.890
I take you for a king.

484
00:38:28.020 --> 00:38:31.140
Kings lack the caution

485
00:38:28.020 --> 00:38:31.140
of common men.

486
00:38:31.270 --> 00:38:32.980
My apologies if I've given offense.

487
00:38:33.100 --> 00:38:35.690
I know how to play a man like Drogo.

488
00:38:35.820 --> 00:38:38.610
I give him a queen

489
00:38:35.820 --> 00:38:38.610
and he gives me an army.

490
00:38:39.530 --> 00:38:41.570
I don't want to be his queen.

491
00:38:46.660 --> 00:38:48.040
I want to go home.

492
00:38:48.700 --> 00:38:50.040
So do I.

493
00:38:51.210 --> 00:38:53.500
I want us both to go home.

494
00:38:53.620 --> 00:38:55.840
but they took it from us.

495
00:38:55.960 --> 00:38:57.750
So tell me. sweet sister.

496
00:38:57.880 --> 00:38:59.550
how do we go home?

497
00:39:02.260 --> 00:39:03.430
I don't know.

498
00:39:03.550 --> 00:39:05.800
We go home with an army.

499
00:39:07.890 --> 00:39:10.180
With Khal Drogo's army.

500
00:39:11.390 --> 00:39:14.400
I would let his whole tribe fuck you.

501
00:39:14.520 --> 00:39:17.610
all 40.000 men and their horses too.

502
00:39:17.730 --> 00:39:19.400
if that's what it took.

503
00:39:26.740 --> 00:39:28.200
(Kisses)

504
00:39:36.710 --> 00:39:39.210
Do you think Joffrey will like me?

505
00:39:39.340 --> 00:39:41.550
What if he thinks I'm ugly?

506
00:39:41.670 --> 00:39:45.090
Then he is the stupidest prince that ever lived.

507
00:39:47.760 --> 00:39:49.100
He's so handsome.

508
00:39:50.260 --> 00:39:52.980
When would we be married?

509
00:39:50.260 --> 00:39:52.980
Soon? Or do we have to wait?

510
00:39:53.100 --> 00:39:56.190
Hush now.

511
00:39:53.100 --> 00:39:56.190
Your father hasn't even said yes.

512
00:39:56.310 --> 00:39:57.980
Why would he say no?

513
00:39:58.110 --> 00:40:01.030
He'd be the second most powerful man

514
00:39:58.110 --> 00:40:01.030
in the kingdoms.

515
00:40:01.150 --> 00:40:03.190
He'd have to leave home.

516
00:40:04.490 --> 00:40:06.860
He'd have to leave me.

517
00:40:07.870 --> 00:40:09.990
And so would you.

518
00:40:10.120 --> 00:40:12.450
You left your home to come here.

519
00:40:12.580 --> 00:40:14.330
And I'd be queen someday.

520
00:40:16.290 --> 00:40:17.830
Please make Father say yes!

521
00:40:17.960 --> 00:40:19.750
- Sansa...

522
00:40:17.960 --> 00:40:19.750
- Please. please!

523
00:40:19.880 --> 00:40:22.760
It's the only thing I ever wanted.

524
00:40:26.800 --> 00:40:28.890
(Music playing. people chattering)

525
00:40:33.180 --> 00:40:34.980
(Laughter)

526
00:40:36.640 --> 00:40:38.810
Fill that up!

527
00:40:36.640 --> 00:40:38.810
Boys. Rodrik. come on.

528
00:40:38.940 --> 00:40:40.980
Come on!

529
00:40:41.110 --> 00:40:43.860
Come here. you little beauty!

530
00:40:43.980 --> 00:40:45.650
(Robert laughing)

531
00:40:59.670 --> 00:41:00.960
Is he dead yet?

532
00:41:06.420 --> 00:41:07.510
Uncle Benjen.

533
00:41:08.720 --> 00:41:10.390
(Laughs)

534
00:41:10.510 --> 00:41:11.720
You got bigger.

535
00:41:13.100 --> 00:41:14.680
Rode all day.

536
00:41:14.810 --> 00:41:17.390
Didn't want to leave you alone

537
00:41:14.810 --> 00:41:17.390
with the Lannisters.

538
00:41:17.520 --> 00:41:18.850
Why aren't you at the feast?

539
00:41:18.980 --> 00:41:21.730
Lady Stark thought it might

540
00:41:18.980 --> 00:41:21.730
insult the royal family

541
00:41:21.860 --> 00:41:23.770
to seat a bastard in their midst.

542
00:41:24.610 --> 00:41:26.990
Well. you're always

543
00:41:24.610 --> 00:41:26.990
welcome on the Wall.

544
00:41:27.110 --> 00:41:29.070
No bastard was ever

545
00:41:27.110 --> 00:41:29.070
refused a seat there.

546
00:41:29.200 --> 00:41:30.910
So take me with you

547
00:41:29.200 --> 00:41:30.910
when you go back.

548
00:41:31.030 --> 00:41:33.910
- Jon...

549
00:41:31.030 --> 00:41:33.910
- Father will let me if you ask him.

550
00:41:34.030 --> 00:41:35.830
I know he will.

551
00:41:38.540 --> 00:41:40.620
The Wall isn't going anywhere.

552
00:41:40.750 --> 00:41:43.420
I'm ready to swear your oath.

553
00:41:43.540 --> 00:41:46.670
You don't understand

554
00:41:43.540 --> 00:41:46.670
what you'd be giving up.

555
00:41:46.800 --> 00:41:48.720
We have no families.

556
00:41:48.840 --> 00:41:52.550
- None of us will ever father sons.

557
00:41:48.840 --> 00:41:52.550
- I don't care about that.

558
00:41:52.680 --> 00:41:55.640
You might. if you knew what it meant.

559
00:41:59.020 --> 00:42:01.480
(Sighs) I'd better get inside.

560
00:42:01.600 --> 00:42:03.900
rescue your father from his guests.

561
00:42:06.940 --> 00:42:08.990
We'll talk later.

562
00:42:17.410 --> 00:42:19.750
(Tyrion) Your uncle's in the Night's Watch.

563
00:42:22.710 --> 00:42:25.040
What are you doing back there?

564
00:42:25.170 --> 00:42:27.380
Preparing for a night with your family.

565
00:42:32.590 --> 00:42:34.510
I've always wanted to see the Wall.

566
00:42:34.640 --> 00:42:36.430
You're Tyrion Lannister.

567
00:42:36.560 --> 00:42:38.100
the queen's brother?

568
00:42:38.220 --> 00:42:39.890
My greatest accomplishment.

569
00:42:41.440 --> 00:42:44.100
And you. you're Ned Stark's bastard.

570
00:42:41.440 --> 00:42:44.100
aren't you?

571
00:42:47.570 --> 00:42:49.740
Did I offend you? Sorry.

572
00:42:51.860 --> 00:42:54.320
You are the bastard. though.

573
00:42:55.620 --> 00:42:57.950
Lord Eddard Stark is my father.

574
00:42:59.200 --> 00:43:01.830
And Lady Stark is not your mother.

575
00:43:01.960 --> 00:43:04.960
making you...the bastard.

576
00:43:06.460 --> 00:43:09.090
Let me give you some advice. bastard.

577
00:43:10.260 --> 00:43:12.050
Never forget what you are.

578
00:43:12.170 --> 00:43:14.510
The rest of the world will not.

579
00:43:14.640 --> 00:43:16.220
Wear it like armor...

580
00:43:17.010 --> 00:43:19.310
and it can never be used to hurt you.

581
00:43:20.970 --> 00:43:23.640
What the hell do you know

582
00:43:20.970 --> 00:43:23.640
about being a bastard?

583
00:43:26.110 --> 00:43:28.570
All dwarves are bastards

584
00:43:26.110 --> 00:43:28.570
in their father's eyes.

585
00:43:44.210 --> 00:43:45.750
(Music playing. chattering)

586
00:43:45.870 --> 00:43:47.460
(Laughter)

587
00:43:50.250 --> 00:43:51.880
You at a feast...

588
00:43:52.840 --> 00:43:54.510
it's like a bear in a trap.

589
00:43:56.510 --> 00:43:58.100
The boy I beheaded...

590
00:43:59.430 --> 00:44:02.350
- did you know him?

591
00:43:59.430 --> 00:44:02.350
- Of course I did. Just a lad.

592
00:44:03.520 --> 00:44:05.600
But he was tough. Ned.

593
00:44:05.730 --> 00:44:06.980
a true ranger.

594
00:44:07.100 --> 00:44:08.610
(Scoffs)

595
00:44:08.730 --> 00:44:10.480
He was talking madness.

596
00:44:11.690 --> 00:44:13.440
Said the walkers slaughtered his friends.

597
00:44:13.570 --> 00:44:15.860
The two he was with are still missing.

598
00:44:17.530 --> 00:44:20.990
Hmph. A wildling ambush.

599
00:44:21.990 --> 00:44:23.080
Maybe.

600
00:44:24.370 --> 00:44:26.920
Direwolves south of the Wall.

601
00:44:27.040 --> 00:44:29.250
talk of the walkers.

602
00:44:29.380 --> 00:44:31.920
and my brother might be

603
00:44:29.380 --> 00:44:31.920
the next Hand of the King.

604
00:44:33.130 --> 00:44:34.970
Winter is coming.

605
00:44:36.590 --> 00:44:38.390
Winter is coming.

606
00:44:38.510 --> 00:44:39.930
(They chuckle)

607
00:44:40.050 --> 00:44:42.890
- Uncle Benjen.

608
00:44:40.050 --> 00:44:42.890
- Robb boy.

609
00:44:43.020 --> 00:44:44.470
- How are you?

610
00:44:43.020 --> 00:44:44.470
- I'm good.

611
00:44:44.600 --> 00:44:46.850
(Laughter)

612
00:44:47.940 --> 00:44:50.690
Is this your first time

613
00:44:47.940 --> 00:44:50.690
in the North. Your Grace?

614
00:44:50.810 --> 00:44:53.570
Yes. Lovely country.

615
00:44:57.360 --> 00:45:00.700
I'm sure it's very grim

616
00:44:57.360 --> 00:45:00.700
after King's Landing.

617
00:45:01.990 --> 00:45:06.370
I remember how scared I was when

618
00:45:01.990 --> 00:45:06.370
Ned brought me up here for the first time.

619
00:45:08.580 --> 00:45:10.170
Hello. little dove.

620
00:45:11.170 --> 00:45:13.340
But you are a beauty.

621
00:45:13.460 --> 00:45:15.760
- How old are you?

622
00:45:13.460 --> 00:45:15.760
- Thirteen. Your Grace.

623
00:45:15.880 --> 00:45:18.470
You're tall. Still growing?

624
00:45:18.590 --> 00:45:20.430
I think so. Your Grace.

625
00:45:20.550 --> 00:45:22.680
And have you bled yet?

626
00:45:27.810 --> 00:45:29.270
No. Your Grace.

627
00:45:30.770 --> 00:45:32.400
Your dress. did you make it?

628
00:45:34.190 --> 00:45:37.440
Such talent.

629
00:45:34.190 --> 00:45:37.440
You must make something for me.

630
00:45:39.360 --> 00:45:42.410
I hear we might share

631
00:45:39.360 --> 00:45:42.410
a grandchild someday.

632
00:45:43.450 --> 00:45:44.620
I hear the same.

633
00:45:44.740 --> 00:45:46.950
Your daughter will do well in the capital.

634
00:45:47.080 --> 00:45:50.420
Such a beauty shouldn't stay

635
00:45:47.080 --> 00:45:50.420
hidden up here forever.

636
00:46:07.430 --> 00:46:10.060
- Your pardon.

637
00:46:07.430 --> 00:46:10.060
- I hear we might be neighbors soon.

638
00:46:10.190 --> 00:46:13.650
- I hope it's true.

639
00:46:10.190 --> 00:46:13.650
- Yes. the king has honored me with his offer.

640
00:46:13.770 --> 00:46:16.980
I'm sure we'll have a tournament to celebrate

641
00:46:13.770 --> 00:46:16.980
your new title. if you accept.

642
00:46:17.110 --> 00:46:19.190
It would be good

643
00:46:17.110 --> 00:46:19.190
to have you on the field.

644
00:46:19.320 --> 00:46:21.700
The competition has become a bit stale.

645
00:46:21.820 --> 00:46:24.070
- I don't fight in tournaments.

646
00:46:21.820 --> 00:46:24.070
- No?

647
00:46:24.200 --> 00:46:25.740
Getting a little old for it?

648
00:46:25.870 --> 00:46:27.580
(Chuckles)

649
00:46:27.700 --> 00:46:29.750
I don't fight in tournaments

650
00:46:29.870 --> 00:46:32.250
because when I fight a man for real.

651
00:46:32.370 --> 00:46:34.130
I don't want him to know what I can do.

652
00:46:36.420 --> 00:46:37.800
Well said.

653
00:46:39.170 --> 00:46:40.510
- (Laughing)

654
00:46:39.170 --> 00:46:40.510
- Arya!

655
00:46:42.840 --> 00:46:44.550
It's not funny!

656
00:46:44.680 --> 00:46:47.310
She always does this.

657
00:46:47.430 --> 00:46:49.850
This was my favorite dress

658
00:46:47.430 --> 00:46:49.850
and she ruined it.

659
00:46:49.980 --> 00:46:52.440
She always does it

660
00:46:49.980 --> 00:46:52.440
and it's not funny!

661
00:46:52.560 --> 00:46:54.400
(Robb) Time for bed.

662
00:46:55.900 --> 00:46:57.480
(Arya groans)

663
00:47:05.490 --> 00:47:07.160
(Ned) I'm a Northman.

664
00:47:08.870 --> 00:47:13.370
I belong here with you. not down south

665
00:47:08.870 --> 00:47:13.370
in that rats' nest they call a capital.

666
00:47:14.420 --> 00:47:17.170
I won't let him take you.

667
00:47:18.710 --> 00:47:21.300
The king takes what he wants.

668
00:47:21.420 --> 00:47:23.720
(Snorts) That's why he's king.

669
00:47:24.760 --> 00:47:28.430
I'll say. "Listen. fat man."

670
00:47:28.560 --> 00:47:29.600
(He laughs)

671
00:47:29.720 --> 00:47:32.850
"You are not taking

672
00:47:29.720 --> 00:47:32.850
my husband anywhere.

673
00:47:32.980 --> 00:47:34.900
"He belongs to me now."

674
00:47:38.650 --> 00:47:40.690
How did he get so fat?

675
00:47:40.820 --> 00:47:45.110
He only stops eating

676
00:47:40.820 --> 00:47:45.110
when it's time for a drink. (Chuckles)

677
00:47:45.240 --> 00:47:46.620
(Knocking)

678
00:47:46.740 --> 00:47:49.160
(Man) It's Maester Luwin. my lord.

679
00:47:50.620 --> 00:47:52.540
Send him in.

680
00:47:54.830 --> 00:47:57.170
Pardon. my lord. my lady.

681
00:47:57.290 --> 00:47:59.800
A rider in the night...

682
00:47:59.920 --> 00:48:02.090
from your sister.

683
00:48:09.810 --> 00:48:12.430
- Stay.

684
00:48:09.810 --> 00:48:12.430
- This was sent from the Eyrie.

685
00:48:12.560 --> 00:48:14.230
(Door closes)

686
00:48:18.440 --> 00:48:20.690
What's she doing at the Eyrie?

687
00:48:20.820 --> 00:48:23.360
She hasn't been back there

688
00:48:20.820 --> 00:48:23.360
since her wedding.

689
00:48:31.830 --> 00:48:33.700
(Ned) What news?

690
00:48:35.330 --> 00:48:37.790
(Catelyn) She's fled the capital.

691
00:48:40.130 --> 00:48:42.670
She says Jon Arryn was murdered.

692
00:48:42.800 --> 00:48:44.670
By the Lannisters.

693
00:48:44.800 --> 00:48:47.470
She says the king is in danger.

694
00:48:47.590 --> 00:48:49.850
She's fresh widowed. Cat.

695
00:48:49.970 --> 00:48:51.600
She doesn't know what she's saying.

696
00:48:51.720 --> 00:48:57.020
Lysa's head would be on a spike right now

697
00:48:51.720 --> 00:48:57.020
if the wrong people had found that letter.

698
00:48:57.140 --> 00:48:59.310
Do you think she would risk her life.

699
00:48:59.440 --> 00:49:01.020
her son's life.

700
00:49:01.150 --> 00:49:04.530
if she wasn't certain

701
00:49:01.150 --> 00:49:04.530
her husband was murdered?

702
00:49:11.740 --> 00:49:13.620
If this news is true...

703
00:49:13.740 --> 00:49:17.290
and the Lannisters conspire

704
00:49:13.740 --> 00:49:17.290
against the throne.

705
00:49:17.410 --> 00:49:19.830
who but you can protect the king?

706
00:49:19.960 --> 00:49:22.210
They murdered the last Hand.

707
00:49:22.340 --> 00:49:24.550
Now you want Ned to take the job?

708
00:49:24.670 --> 00:49:28.550
The king rode for a month

709
00:49:24.670 --> 00:49:28.550
to ask for Lord Stark's help.

710
00:49:28.680 --> 00:49:31.180
He's the only one he trusts.

711
00:49:32.680 --> 00:49:35.520
You swore the king an oath. my lord.

712
00:49:35.640 --> 00:49:39.230
He's spent half his life

713
00:49:35.640 --> 00:49:39.230
fighting Robert's wars.

714
00:49:39.350 --> 00:49:41.350
He owes him nothing.

715
00:49:43.270 --> 00:49:46.490
Your father and brother

716
00:49:43.270 --> 00:49:46.490
rode south once

717
00:49:46.610 --> 00:49:49.240
on a king's demand.

718
00:49:51.160 --> 00:49:53.280
A different time.

719
00:49:54.660 --> 00:49:56.750
A different king.

720
00:50:00.290 --> 00:50:02.290
- (Noisy chatter)

721
00:50:00.290 --> 00:50:02.290
- (Drumming)

722
00:50:23.560 --> 00:50:25.520
(Hissing)

723
00:50:30.740 --> 00:50:32.740
(Gasps)

724
00:50:57.930 --> 00:51:01.430
When do I meet with the khal?

725
00:50:57.930 --> 00:51:01.430
We need to begin planning the invasion.

726
00:51:01.560 --> 00:51:04.980
If Khal Drogo has promised you a crown.

727
00:51:01.560 --> 00:51:04.980
you shall have it.

728
00:51:05.110 --> 00:51:08.150
- When?

729
00:51:05.110 --> 00:51:08.150
- When their omens favor war.

730
00:51:09.280 --> 00:51:11.820
I piss on Dothraki omens.

731
00:51:11.950 --> 00:51:14.610
I've waited 17 years to get my throne back.

732
00:51:23.960 --> 00:51:26.960
- (Crowd ululating)

733
00:51:23.960 --> 00:51:26.960
- (Grunting)

734
00:51:41.470 --> 00:51:42.770
(Cheering)

735
00:51:52.400 --> 00:51:54.360
(Speaks Dothraki)

736
00:51:54.490 --> 00:51:55.950
(Blades clang)

737
00:52:05.500 --> 00:52:06.830
(Screams)

738
00:52:14.550 --> 00:52:19.510
A Dothraki wedding without at least

739
00:52:14.550 --> 00:52:19.510
three deaths is considered a dull affair.

740
00:52:20.890 --> 00:52:23.180
(Laughing)

741
00:52:32.230 --> 00:52:34.240
(Speaks Dothraki)

742
00:52:34.360 --> 00:52:36.150
(Speaks Dothraki)

743
00:52:41.870 --> 00:52:44.910
A small gift. for the new khaleesi.

744
00:52:45.870 --> 00:52:48.460
Songs and histories from the Seven Kingdoms.

745
00:52:50.130 --> 00:52:51.540
Thank you. ser.

746
00:52:53.250 --> 00:52:55.920
Are you from my country?

747
00:52:56.050 --> 00:52:58.090
Ser Jorah Mormont of Bear Island.

748
00:52:58.220 --> 00:53:00.930
I served your father for many years.

749
00:53:01.050 --> 00:53:04.020
Gods be good. I hope to

750
00:53:01.050 --> 00:53:04.020
always serve the rightful king.

751
00:53:27.250 --> 00:53:29.920
Dragon's eggs. Daenerys.

752
00:53:30.040 --> 00:53:32.790
from the Shadow Lands beyond Asshai.

753
00:53:32.920 --> 00:53:35.840
The ages have turned them to stone.

754
00:53:35.960 --> 00:53:37.920
but they will always be beautiful.

755
00:53:40.180 --> 00:53:41.850
Thank you. Magister.

756
00:54:50.540 --> 00:54:52.580
She's beautiful.

757
00:54:56.840 --> 00:54:58.090
Ser Jorah. I...

758
00:54:58.210 --> 00:55:00.970
I don't know how to say "thank you"

759
00:54:58.210 --> 00:55:00.970
in Dothraki.

760
00:55:01.090 --> 00:55:03.890
There is no word for "thank you"

761
00:55:01.090 --> 00:55:03.890
in Dothraki.

762
00:55:25.070 --> 00:55:27.030
Make him happy.

763
00:55:39.550 --> 00:55:41.210
(Waves crashing)

764
00:56:26.430 --> 00:56:28.430
- No.

765
00:56:26.430 --> 00:56:28.430
- (Sobs)

766
00:56:31.760 --> 00:56:33.600
Do you know the common tongue?

767
00:56:38.440 --> 00:56:40.150
- (Pin clanks)

768
00:56:38.440 --> 00:56:40.150
- No.

769
00:56:44.400 --> 00:56:46.610
Is "no" the only word that you know?

770
00:56:48.110 --> 00:56:49.450
No.

771
00:56:55.080 --> 00:56:57.170
(Continues sobbing)

772
00:57:17.810 --> 00:57:19.850
Rough night. Imp?

773
00:57:19.980 --> 00:57:21.940
If I get through this without squirting

774
00:57:22.070 --> 00:57:24.940
from one end or the other.

775
00:57:22.070 --> 00:57:24.940
it'll be a miracle.

776
00:57:25.070 --> 00:57:26.860
I didn't pick you for a hunter.

777
00:57:26.990 --> 00:57:30.070
The greatest in the land -

778
00:57:26.990 --> 00:57:30.070
my spear never misses.

779
00:57:31.160 --> 00:57:33.120
It's not hunting if you pay for it.

780
00:57:42.170 --> 00:57:44.210
Are you as good with a spear

781
00:57:42.170 --> 00:57:44.210
as you used to be?

782
00:57:44.340 --> 00:57:46.800
No. but I'm still better than you.

783
00:57:46.920 --> 00:57:48.720
(Laughs)

784
00:57:49.800 --> 00:57:51.430
I know what I'm putting you through.

785
00:57:51.550 --> 00:57:53.220
Thank you for saying yes.

786
00:57:55.350 --> 00:57:57.640
I only ask you because I need you.

787
00:57:58.850 --> 00:58:01.400
You're a loyal friend. You hear me?

788
00:58:02.480 --> 00:58:04.070
A loyal friend.

789
00:58:04.190 --> 00:58:05.860
The last one I've got.

790
00:58:07.610 --> 00:58:09.780
- I hope I'll serve you well.

791
00:58:07.610 --> 00:58:09.780
- You will.

792
00:58:11.070 --> 00:58:14.280
And I'll make sure you don't look

793
00:58:11.070 --> 00:58:14.280
so fucking grim all the time.

794
00:58:15.620 --> 00:58:17.870
Come on. boys.

795
00:58:15.620 --> 00:58:17.870
let's go kill some boar!

796
00:58:28.090 --> 00:58:29.590
Come on. you.

797
00:58:44.650 --> 00:58:45.980
(Whines)

798
00:58:54.910 --> 00:58:56.490
(Grunts)

799
00:59:00.410 --> 00:59:02.250
(Barks softly)

800
00:59:08.760 --> 00:59:10.420
(Woman gasping)

801
00:59:14.680 --> 00:59:16.300
(Woman moaning)

802
00:59:26.440 --> 00:59:28.110
(Grunting. moaning)

803
00:59:44.370 --> 00:59:45.830
(Gasps)

804
00:59:45.960 --> 00:59:48.750
- Stop! Stop.

805
00:59:45.960 --> 00:59:48.750
- (Gasps)

806
00:59:53.630 --> 00:59:55.890
Are you completely mad?

807
00:59:56.010 --> 00:59:58.510
- He saw us.

808
00:59:56.010 --> 00:59:58.510
- It's all right. it's all right.

809
00:59:58.640 --> 01:00:00.680
- It's all right.

810
00:59:58.640 --> 01:00:00.680
- He saw us!

811
01:00:00.810 --> 01:00:02.930
I heard you the first time.

812
01:00:04.140 --> 01:00:05.730
(Whimpers)

813
01:00:07.690 --> 01:00:09.360
Quite the little climber. aren't you?

814
01:00:10.650 --> 01:00:13.440
- How old are you. boy?

815
01:00:10.650 --> 01:00:13.440
- Ten.

816
01:00:13.570 --> 01:00:15.150
Ten.

817
01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:26.330
- The things I do for love.

818
01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:26.330
- (Gasps)
